Detailed Description

Structure represents USB SSP controller resources. That structure must be aligned to USBSSP_PAGE_SIZE because of xhciResources.

Field Documentation

uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::actualdeviceSlot

Keeps actual device slot, when USBSSP works in device mode it is 1

uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::actualPort

Keeps port ID

CH9_UsbSpeed USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::actualSpeed

Keeps actual speed the port operate in

Command queue object

uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::connected

Reflects actual state of Current Connect Status of PORTSC register, 0 - disconnected, 1 - connected

uint32_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::contextEntries

Stores actual value of context Entry

uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::devAddress

Keep device address sent during SET_ADDRESS setup request - is active only in device mode

uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::devConfigFlag

uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::deviceModeFlag

1 - USB SSP works in device mode, 0 - host mode

uint32_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::enabledEndpsMask

Mask with enabled endpoints for last SET_CONFIGURATION request

Remarks
Follows InputControlContext.DWORD1
uint8_t USBSSP_DriverResourcesT_s::enableSlotPending

Indicates whether ENABLE_SLOT_COMMAND was sent but slot ID has not been set yet
